overview: The user initiated a task to fix numerous issues in a pull request,
  including critical security vulnerabilities and broken Vercel deployments. The
  agent began by thoroughly reviewing PR comments and CI failures. It
  systematically addressed lint errors, upgraded the insecure 'true' cookie
  authentication to a robust HMAC-based session system, and implemented input
  validation for API routes and pagination for CSV exports. Key bug fixes
  included correcting PDF metric calculations, enabling null values in number
  fields, wiring up the PDF download button, and removing hardcoded user names.
  A significant challenge was ensuring authentication worked in Vercel's Edge
  Runtime, leading to a refactor of the crypto functions to use the Web Crypto
  API. Despite these code fixes, Vercel deploys continued to fail, and the agent
  ultimately identified a missing database URL configuration in the Prisma
  schema as the underlying problem.
